TY  - JOUR
AU  - Riedel, Frank
T1  - Decreasing Yield Curves in a Model with an Unknown Constant Growth Rate
PY  - 2000
Y1  - 2000/01/01
DO  - 10.1023/A:1009833908681
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 4
IS  - 1
SP  - 51
EP  - 67
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - The effect of incomplete information on the term structure of interest rates is examined in the framework of a pure exchange economy under uncertainty where aggregate output grows at a constant rate. If the growth rate is known, the term structure is flat. In contrast, the term structure is a decreasing curve when agents do not know the growth rate. Long term yields are less than the short rate and the yield of long term bonds is determined by the worst possible realizations of future short rates. JEL classification codes: D5, D9, E4, G1.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1009833908681
ER  - 



